<p><font>Volupine, from <em>voluptas </em>and
        "pine," is the personification of Venice, who
        is traditionally represented in poetry as a woman. Eliot
        suitably names her "decaying beauty." Princess
        is, among others, a euphemism for whore.</font></p>
